.jumbotron
  .container
    %h2
      Double Union is a hacker/maker space for women in San Francisco.
    %p
      Our mission is to
      create a community workshop where women can work on projects in a comfortable, welcoming
      environment.
    %p.last
      = link_to 'Join us', membership_path, :class => 'btn btn-primary btn-lg'
      = link_to 'Support us', support_path, :class => 'btn btn-default btn-lg'

.container
  .row
    .col-md-12.text-center
      %h3 Double Union is a space for your projects
    .col-md-6
      %p
        Things women do in this space include sewing, programming, electronics,
        woodworking, fiber arts of all kinds, and zine making.
    .col-md-3
      .thumbnail
        =image_tag 'tools/lightbox-and-dremel.jpg'
    .col-md-3
      .thumbnail
        =image_tag 'tools/yarn-and-screenprinting-supplies.jpg'

  .row
    .col-md-3
      .thumbnail
        =image_tag 'tools/tools-table.jpg'
    .col-md-3
      .thumbnail
        =image_tag 'tools/paper-cutter.jpg'
    .col-md-6
      %p
        Fast internet, shared tools, a carefully curated library of books and zines, and discussion spaces make this a great space for working on your projects, learning skills, and meeting new friends.

        
  .row
    .col-md-6
      %p
        Double Union is a supportive community for feminist activism. We are intersectional
        feminists, women-centered, and queer and trans-inclusive.

  .row
    .col-md-12.text-center
      %h3 Visiting Double Union: Classes, Open Houses and Events
    .col-md-6
      %p
        Double Union is in the heart of San Francisco, located on Valencia Street between 14th Street and 15th Street, between Four Barrel Coffee and Zeitgeist.
    .col-md-6.col-md-offset-6
      %p
        Other than during events open to the public, Double Union visitors must be the invited guest of a member. Please do not visit without the express invitation of a member. Please do not invite guests unless you are a member. Guests may be any gender or age.
    .col-md-6
      %p
        Open house events are open to the general public. Visitors do not need an invitation from a member to attend an open house, and may be any gender or age. We will announce when we start having open houses.

  .row
    .col-md-6.col-md-offset-6
      %p
        You can learn more about us by reading our
        = "#{link_to 'blog', tumblr_posts_path},".html_safe
        following us on Twitter at
        = "#{link_to "@#{TWITTER_USERNAME}", TWITTER_URL, :target => '_blank'},".html_safe
        or joining our #{ link_to "general interest mailing list", "http://lists.doubleunion.org/listinfo.cgi/doubleunion-doubleunion.org" }.

  .row
    .col-md-12.text-center
      %h3
        Want to Support Double Union?
    .col-md-6

      %p
        Double Union is a non-profit supported entirely by donations, membership dues, donations, and volunteers.

      %p
        We would love your support in creating a women-friendly makerspace in San Francisco! We hope to serve as a role model and resource for other makerspaces and hackerspaces around the world.

      %p We are so grateful to #{link_to "our supporters", supporters_path} for helping us thrive!

    .col-md-6.col-md-6-offset-6.well

      %h4
        Want to make a one time donation?
      %p
        Sending money via Paypal to
        = PAYPAL_EMAIL
        is the easiest way for you to help us build an amazing space for women.

      %h4
        Can you support our work each month?
      = render "shared/donate_monthly"
